  "feedback": "## #615 Iter-3 Review — NOT CLEAN\n\nAll four specialists ran in parallel. Two new blocking items surfaced; the scope is not clear for merge.\n\n---\n\n### Overall Ratings\n\n| Specialist | Rating | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n| lifecycle-state-machine | 2/5 | ❌ New blocker |\n| gui-frontend | 3/5 | ⚠️ New regression |\n| test-coverage | 3/5 | ⚠️ Gaps |\n| security | 4/5 | ✅ Clean (W only) |\n\n---\n\n### B-NEW (Blocking) — Primary-slot rebind bypasses pre-validate 409\n\n**File:** `src/clawrium/gui/routes/providers.py:565`\n\nThe B3 fix guards the pre-validate block with `body.role != PRIMARY_ROLE`. A different provider submitting `role='primary'` when a primary is already attached skips the block entirely → falls through `_persist_attachments` → `validate()` → `AttachmentError` → **HTTP 400**, not 409. The blocking-provider name is absent from the 400 body. Three reviewers flagged this independently (lifecycle, security suggestion, test-coverage warning).\n\n**Fix:** Remove `body.role != PRIMARY_ROLE` from line 565's condition. Handle primary branch: `f'hermes primary slot is already bound to {_attachment_name(occupant)!r}; detach first'`. Add test: fixture with `anth` as primary → attach `alt` with `role='primary'` → assert 409 + `'primary'` + `'anth'` in detail.\n\n---\n\n### Frontend Regression (Warning → treat as blocking for UX) — Orphaned `\u003clabel htmlFor\u003e`\n\n**File:** `gui/src/components/providers/attach-provider-modal.tsx:107-134`\n\nWhen `noAvailableRoles=true`, the `\u003clabel htmlFor={roleId}\u003e` renders but the `\u003cselect id={roleId}\u003e` does not exist. The `htmlFor` points to a nonexistent element. AT users clicking \"Role\" focus nothing. The existing test (`queryByLabelText('Role') === null`) passes because the select is absent but does NOT assert the label is also absent — the regression is untested.\n\n**Fix (option a):** Wrap the label in the same `noAvailableRoles` conditional. Add assertion: `expect(screen.queryByText('Role')).toBeNull()` in the all-aux-filled describe block.\n\n---\n\n### W2 / W3 / W4 — Deferred callouts are commit-message-only\n\nAll three deferrals exist only in the git commit message. No inline `TODO` comment in source.\n\n| Item | File | Required annotation |\n|---|---|---|\n| W2 (aria-describedby) | `agent-attachments-card.tsx:174` | `{/* TODO(#615-W2): span title not announced by AT — follow-up */}` |\n| W3 (TOCTOU) | `providers.py` above line 524 | `# W3 (TOCTOU): idempotent+conflict checks read current outside update_host lock — deferred to dedicated refactor.` |\n| W4 (structured 409) | same block | `# W4 (structured 409): detail is free-form prose; structured body deferred to follow-up.` |\n\n---\n\n### B3 Test Gap — No state-unchanged assertion\n\n**File:** `tests/test_gui_route_provider_attach.py:343`\n\n`test_attach_hermes_different_provider_same_slot_409` asserts 409 + body but not that `state['host']['agents']['sage']['providers']` is unchanged. Add:\n```python\nassert len(state['host']['agents']['sage']['providers']) == 2  # no write occurred\n```\n\n---\n\n### Confirmed Clean ✅\n\n| Item | Verdict |\n|---|---|\n| B2 (primary assertion in rebind 409) | Clean — test pins `'primary'` and `'detach'` in body |\n| B3 aux-slot path | Clean — pre-validate fires before any write, body names blocking provider |\n| W1 (per-row detach disable) | Clean — `isPrimary \u0026\u0026 auxCount \u003e 0` scopes correctly; in-flight global disable is intentional race guard |\n| W6 (all-aux-filled HTTP test) | Clean — asserts 409 + meaningful body |\n| W7 (404 detail) | Clean — identifying name in detail for all three 404 paths |\n| B1 / W5 / W8 (out-of-scope) | Untouched, confirmed |\n| Auth boundary | Clean — no bypass of token/SSH boundary |\n| Secrets in frontend | Clean — `has_api_key` boolean only, no credentials exposed |\n\n---\n\n### Required for Iter-4\n\n1. **B-NEW** — Remove `body.role != PRIMARY_ROLE` from line 565; return 409 for primary-slot collision with occupant name; add test.\n2. **Orphaned label** — Conditional render of `\u003clabel\u003e` in `attach-provider-modal.tsx`; add test assertion.\n3. **Inline callouts** — Add `TODO` comments for W2, W3, W4 in source (not just commit message).\n4. **B3 state assertion** — One-line post-rejection `len(providers) == 2` check.\n\nIter-4 scope is tight — the blocker is a two-line backend fix + one test + one frontend conditional + three comments. The rest of the deferred items (W3 TOCTOU actual fix, W4 structured 409, HTTP 500 test) remain correctly out-of-scope for this PR.\n",
