n\": \"gui/src/components/providers/attach-provider-modal.tsx:107-134\",\n      \"issue\": \"New regression: orphaned \u003clabel htmlFor={roleId}\u003e when all auxiliary slots are filled. The label on line 107-111 always renders when `supportsMulti` is true. When `noAvailableRoles` is true (line 113), the branch renders a `\u003cp\u003e` without `id={roleId}`, so the label's `htmlFor` points to a nonexistent element. AT users clicking 'Role' focus nothing; the broken association also violates HTML semantics. The test at attach-provider-modal.test.tsx line 199 (`queryByLabelText('Role') === null`) passes because the select doesn't exist, but it does NOT assert that the orphan label is also absent — so the bug is untested.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Two options: (a) wrap the label in the same `{noAvailableRoles ? ... : ...}` conditional so it only renders alongside the select; or (b) give the `\u003cp\u003e` `id={roleId}` and change the label's `htmlFor` to be conditional. Option (a) is simpler. Add a test assertion: `expect(screen.queryByText('Role')).toBeNull()` in the all-aux-filled describe block.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"gui/src/components/providers/attach-provider-modal.tsx:56-57\",\n      \"issue\": \"State variable `role` is not reset when `open` transitions false→true (only reset in `handleClose`). If the parent closes the modal programmatically (e.g. on successful attach via `setModalOpen(false)` at agent-attachments-card.tsx:80) without calling `onClose`, the `role` state retains its previous value. On re-open, `effectiveRole` would be the stale role if `availableRoles.length !== 1`.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add a `useEffect(() =\u003e { if (!open) { setProviderName(''); setRole(''); } }, [open])` so close-from-parent also resets form state. The parent does call `onClose` on explicit cancel, but the success path calls `setModalOpen(false)` directly at line 80 of the card without going through `handleClose`.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"gui/src/components/providers/agent-attachments-card.tsx:66-70\",\n      \"issue\": \"eslint-disable-next-line on the useEffect deps is correct (refresh is a local async function that closes over agentName), but the comment says 'agentName is the only input' without noting that refresh itself is not memoized — if it were ever extracted, the disable would mask a real miss. Low risk as-is.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Acceptable as-is. If refresh is ever lifted to a custom hook, remove the eslint disable and add agentName to deps explicitly.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"Add inline W2 TODO comment at agent-attachments-card.tsx:174 — the commit message is not a substitute for in-source deferred annotations.\",\n    \"Fix orphaned \u003clabel htmlFor={roleId}\u003e in attach-provider-modal.tsx: hide the label when noAvailableRoles is true, and add an assertion to the all-aux-filled test that the 'Role' label is absent from the DOM.\",\n    \"Fix state leak: programmatic modal close (success path) bypasses handleClose and leaves role/providerName stale for the next open. Add a useEffect on `open` to reset.\",\n    \"B1 (CLI test #612 / PR #616), W5 (CLI detach test), W8 (clawctl agent get first-only) are all untouched — correctly out of scope.\"\n  ],\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"files_reviewed\": 5,\n    \"domain\": \"gui/frontend\",\n    \"w1_status\": \"correctly fixed — conflict-based disable is per-row (primary only); in-flight global disable is intentional iter-2 fix\",\n    \"w2_callout_in_source\": false,\n    \"w2_callout_in_commit\": true,\n    \"out_of_scope_clean\": true,\n    \"new_regression\": \"orphaned htmlFor label in attach-provider-modal when noAvailableRoles=true\"\n  }\n}\n\u003c/output\u003e",
